{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dd7b0622-ab17-42a8-82af-d617a850678c","content":"\n\n","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_x7i2SXWgRGHlqwQxHVR0VS","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Reviewing project context"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_6x1RlbzdSQaMbFQ3vazSBz","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-ed781ab337264d9fbc91a1f168f657bd/TestProject.csproj"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-ed781ab337264d9fbc91a1f168f657bd/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"c0774ee6-41fe-42fa-89d8-9b57c812c0ff","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change between MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 and MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0 related to test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes, not a code change request.\n\nLet me look at what's in their project files to understand context, but I likely know the answer already.\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4+, the default test runner changed from VSTest to Microsoft Testing Platform (MTP). In MSTest.Sdk 4.0+, the VSTest compatibility layer was removed entirely. This means `vstest.console` can no longer discover or run tests built with MSTest.Sdk 4.1.0.\n\n\nI should verify this against their actual project configuration to make sure I'm giving them accurate information.","outputTokens":308},"id":"1fb7038b-b8ea-403d-aba6-304598a95b5f","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:28:32.704Z","parentId":"dd5b64ca-53ff-427b-825a-168eab009b78"}
