{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c3d33df3-0212-4ec5-b730-8d1675163662","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility layer.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk **3.4**, the default runner switched from VSTest to **Microsoft Testing Platform (MTP)**. The VSTest bridge was still included so tools like `vstest.console` kept working. In **4.0+**, that bridge was removed entirely.\n\nYour options:\n\n1. **Switch your CI to the MTP runner** (recommended):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test          # works natively with MTP\n   # or run the test exe directly:\n   ./TestProject --report-trx\n   ```\n\n2. **Re-enable the VSTest bridge** if you must keep `vstest.console`:\n   Add this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   <ItemGroup>\n     <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge\" />\n   </ItemGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Pin to the older SDK** temporarily:\n   ```xml\n   <Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n   ```\n\nOption 1 is the intended path forward — `dotnet test` already supports MTP natively and is the recommended way to run tests with MSTest.Sdk 4.x.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c0774ee6-41fe-42fa-89d8-9b57c812c0ff","outputTokens":340},"id":"38527af5-8cfa-4168-994b-59551bc462e7","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:28:41.032Z","parentId":"35ba74d7-b462-48ec-bd2a-949aae92bfba"}
